3. COMMERCIAL USE AND COMMERCIAL LICENSE

3.1. Commercial Use Defined

"Commercial Use" means use of the Software, in whole or in part, in any of
the following contexts:
  (a) incorporation into a product, service, or system that is sold,
      licensed, or made available for a fee or other consideration to
      third parties;
  (b) use by a for-profit entity in the production, delivery, or operation
      of revenue-generating products or services;
  (c) use by a government entity in connection with services for which
      fees are charged to citizens, businesses, or other governments;
  (d) use in any context where the Software materially contributes to the
      generation of revenue.

3.2. Commercial License Required

Commercial Use of the Software requires a separate written commercial
license from the author, EXCEPT where the use qualifies as a Permitted
Free Use under Section 4. Commercial Use without such a license, and
outside the scope of Section 4, constitutes a material breach of this
License.

3.3. Obtaining a Commercial License

Commercial licenses are available from the author on terms to be
negotiated, typically varying with organization size, scope of use,
number of deployments, and duration. To inquire, contact:

    <commercial-licensing contact to be provided by the author>

The author retains sole discretion over the terms offered, subject to
non-discrimination principles consistent with Section 2(d).

3.4. Effect on Distribution Chain

A commercial license issued to one entity does NOT confer commercial
rights on its customers, contractors, or affiliates. Each entity making
Commercial Use of the Software must hold its own commercial license,
unless the use qualifies as a Permitted Free Use.

